 population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William De Sparham was born about 1364, in Sparham, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom, his father, John De Sparham, was 26 and his mother, Beatrice Yermouth, was 23. He had at least 1 daughter with Alis Brosyard."},"et":{"Abt 1364–":"umbes 1364–Surnud","1364–Male":"1364–Surnud","1365–1410":"1365–1410","1409–1450":"1409–1450","1380–Female":"1380–Surnud","1392–Female":"1392–Surnud","1340–Male":"1340–Surnud","1343–Female":"1343–Surnud","ABT 1363":"umbes 1363","1410":"1410","Abt 1364":"umbes 1364","1365":"1365","1343":"1343","1364":"1364","1340":"1340","1450":"1450","1409":"1409","1392":"1392","1380":"1380","Crostwick, Norfolkshire, England":"Crostwick, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sparham, Norfolk, England":"Sparham, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1364–":"noin 1364–Kuollut","1364–Male":"1364–Kuollut","1365–1410":"1365–1410","1409–1450":"1409–1450","1380–Female":"1380–Kuollut","1392–Female":"1392–Kuollut","1340–Male":"1340–Kuollut","1343–Female":"1343–Kuollut","ABT 1363":"noin 1363","1410":"1410","Abt 1364":"noin 1364","1365":"1365","1343":"1343","1364":"1364","1340":"1340","1450":"1450","1409":"1409","1392":"1392","1380":"1380","Crostwick, Norfolkshire, England":"Crostwick, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Sparham, Norfolk, England":"Sparham, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1364–":"environ 1364–Décédé","1364–Male":"1364–Décédé","1365–1410":"1365–1410","1409–1450":"1409–1450","1380–Female":"1380–Décédée","1392–Female":"1392–Décédée","1340–Male":"1340–Décédé","1343–Female":"1343–Décédée","ABT 1363":"environ 1363","1410":"1410","Abt 1364":"environ 1364","1365":"1365","1343":"1343","1364":"1364"